Alfred Zeisler https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred_Zeisler 0 Alfred Zeisler (September 26, 1892 – March 1, 1985) was an American-born German film producer, director, actor and screenwriter. He produced 29 films between 1927 and 1936. He also directed 16 films between 1924 and 1949. He was born in Chicago, Illinois and died in Camano Island, Washington.
